4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that helps individuals become cybersecurity specialists, even without prior knowledge. The program focuses on building a strong foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills in securing these environments. Participants will also learn about cloud security, penetration testing (both offensive and defensive), and cyber threat intelligence analysis. Additionally, the program covers managing risks using data loss prevention strategies and navigating compliance with international standards like ISO 27001 and NIST. The bootcamp lasts for 16 weeks, with 3 live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people. Upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate, recognized by multiple institutions. No previous experience is required to enroll in the program. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit the website at https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop